   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Form Load</uicontrol> event enables you to set values and attributes on a form after the form is generated. The logic is executed when you click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">New</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Edit</uicontrol>, or <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">View</uicontrol> the record, and the execution is completed when the form is generated.</p>
      <p product="Include_PG_Content" class="- topic/p ">
         <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Use Case# Set the value for a field based on user role</uicontrol>
      </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">In the RFI form, if you want the company of the contractor to display automatically when a contractor is creating any record, then you can use the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Form Load</uicontrol> event to set the value for the appropriate field based on the user role.</p>
